Cryptomator is offered for all major platforms (including Android and iOS). Cryptomator encrypts file contents and names using the widespread industry standard AES. Your passphrase is protected against brute forcing attempts using scrypt. Additionally, directory structures get obfuscated. For more info about the Cryptomator encryption scheme, check out the online documentation. Cryptomator is a free and open-source software licensed under the GPLv3. This allows anyone to check our code. Thus, it is impossible to introduce backdoors for third parties or to hide vulnerabilities, so you do not need to trust Cryptomator. Also, vendor lock-ins are impossible. Even if we decided to stop development: The source code is already cloned by hundreds of other developers and development can be picked up by othersgversionl1.17.0-beta1ldownload_urlxrhttps://github.com/cryptomator/cryptomator/releases/download/1.17.0-beta1/cryptomator-1.17.0-beta1-x86_64.AppImagedsizeh53.81 MBhsrc_urlsĀx3https://github.com/cryptomator/cryptomator/releaseshweb_urlsĀxhttps://github.com/cryptomatorhprovideskcryptomatorglicenseĀpGPL-3.0-or-laterkmaintainersx9AppImage (https://github.com/AppImage/appimage.github.io)enotesáx:[EXTERNAL] (This is an unofficial, third-party repository)xI[UNTRUSTED] (We CAN NOT guarantee the authenticity, validity or security)x2This data was autogenerated & is likely inaccuratex/Data used: https://appimage.github.io/feed.jsonx;Provided by: https://github.com/AppImage/appimage.github.ioxNLearn More: https://docs.pkgforge.dev/repositories/external/appimage.github.iox;Please create an Issue or send a PR for an official Packageģcpkgocryptr.appimagehpkg_namefcryptrfpkg_idxappimage.github.io.Cryptr.adobediconx~https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AppImage/appimage.github.io/refs/heads/master/database/icons/Cryptr/icons/128x128/cryptr.pngkdescriptionoA GUI for Vaultgversionfv0.6.0ldownload_urlxNhttps://github.com/adobe/cryptr/releases/download/v0.6.0/Cryptr-0.6.0.AppImagedsizei104.0